column24: The laminate bubbled, then popped at about 1 minute causing a spike in mass data. There were intermittant candle-sized flames prior to ignition. Marked ignition began as a candle sized flame near center of sample, and remained steady for about 2.5 minutes until extinguishing at 7:42. The spark ignitor was reinserted, and reignition occurred at 9:30, and flames spread across the entire sample surface and sustained until end of test.

column24: A few seconds prior to ignition the laminate inflated, then popped violently, causing a spike in mass data. The inflation of the laminate pushed the wire grid upwards, approaching the spark ignitor. The flames extinguished at around 2:50. The spark ignitor was reinserted, and reignition occurred at around 8:45. Test ended after 60 minutes, per ASTM criteria.

column24: At approximately 90 seconds a candle sized flame ignited near the center of the sample, then extinguished a few seconds later. Ignition began at approximately 9 minutes as a candle sized flame at the edge of the sample, which slowly spread along the edges. The ignition event was recorded when the majority of the surface area was involved. By the time of ignition, the sample corners had slightly curled upwards, impacting the spark ignitor as it was removed and causing a spike in mass data.
